This beauty is 6 years old today! Happy Birthday Beckham, we love you! 🥳

NHL OFF SEASON = MUSKOKA 

Many NHL players already call Muskoka home full time in the off season and many more are finding their way here every summer! We are only just getting started! 

After grinding for 82 games and potentially the gruelling play offs, it’s important to enjoy some time off and enjoy life. Muskoka has been a prime vacation spot for NHL players for years but previously they have had to travel back and fourth to the city to skate and train. For the last few years, lead by founder Sam Gagner @muskokahockey has made it possible for them to maximize their off season by bringing their training ground to cottage country. Players have access to world class on and off ice training through Muskoka Hockey and it’s partners. The days of travelling to the city are over for many. Their days consist of on and off ice training in the mornings and it’s in the boat or on the course ⛳️ before 2pm everyday! 

We integrated some video from our friends @waterfrontmuskoka to showcase the Muskoka lifestyle. Make sure you give them a follow! 

Videos don’t do is justice! Come find out for yourselves!

#nhl #muskoka #training #hockey #muskokahockey

Deceptive Catch and Release - Inside and Outside 
@sgagner89 
Being able to get shots through is a mastered skill. Changing the shot angle and finding open space, often shooting around an opponent. 

If you want to score more goals and create more secondary chances for your team, master how to get shots through traffic!

Add a pass,
Threaten shot with your eyes and body, shift back and pass it back. 

The next step is to add token pressure. 

Remember if you’re right handed you’re shooting off your right leg when pushing to the inside. Lefty’s shoot off your left leg. 

Gain control of the puck, push to the inside while shifting your weight and load inside leg and let it rip!

Sam Gagner's (@sgagner89) back on the ice with the @edmontonoilers! 🥺

6 months ago @sgagner89 went through double hip surgery, many thought his career might be over… but Sam had other plans! 

What a comeback, and he is only just getting started!

This is only a brief look into a long gruelling journey back to the NHL. It was months of relentless therapy. Surrounded by a great team, the come back was on and Sam was taking it personally

This is a prime example of how Sam has managed to play over 1000 games in the @nhl and still going strong! 

Though the Oilers fell short in his comeback appearance, it was an extremely special moment and we believe that he will play a pivotal role in the @edmontonoilers success moving forward!
#89 for the Edmonton Oilers @muskokahockey @torontomarlboros @fireflyrecovery
